---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Glow Intel — skincare content by Angelo, a web developer and skincare business owner."
>
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">About Glow Intel</h1>

      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          I'm Angelo. I'm a freelance web developer and I run a skincare business. Glow Intel is where I write about what I've actually learned — from the science, from building products, and from years of testing things on my own skin.
        </p>

        <p>
          I started this site because most skincare content online is either too surface-level, too sponsored, or just recycling whatever is trending on TikTok. I wanted a place for the real take.
        </p>

        <h2>What I believe</h2>

        <p>
          Less is more. A solid 3-4 product routine with scientific backing beats a 10-step stack every time. The fewer variables in your routine, the easier it is to know what's actually working.
        </p>

        <p>
          Science matters, but I'm not academic about it. If an ingredient has solid research behind it, I'll recommend it. If it's mostly marketing, I'll say that. I don't care if a brand is popular — I care if it works.
        </p>

        <p>
          Honest beats nice. If a product is overpriced for what it does, I'll tell you. If a trendy ingredient is mostly hype, I'll tell you that too. You deserve the real take, not the PR-approved version.
        </p>

        <h2>What you'll find here</h2>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Ingredient breakdowns</strong> — what the science actually says about retinol, niacinamide, vitamin C, and more</li>
          <li><strong>Honest reviews</strong> — no sponsored content, no affiliate pressure</li>
          <li><strong>Versus articles</strong> — direct comparisons so you can make a real decision</li>
          <li><strong>Routines</strong> — practical advice for real skin types, not the airbrushed ideal</li>
          <li><strong>Beauty business</strong> — for anyone thinking about the ecommerce side of skincare</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Get in touch</h2>

        <p>
          Questions, pitches, or corrections? Send me an email at <a href="mailto:hello@glowintel.com">hello@glowintel.com</a>. I read everything.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
